      • generateKeywordId

        public java.lang.String generateKeywordId(java.lang.String keyword)
        Generates Id for this keyword . If keyword doesnt exist in the keyword_ids , new id is created and also inserted into keyword table
        Parameters:
        keyword - - keyword Text
        Returns:
        - generated Id for give keyword

      • generateConferenceId

        public java.lang.String generateConferenceId(java.lang.String confDate,
                                    java.lang.String confName,
                                    java.lang.String confNum,
                                    java.lang.String confLoc,
                                    java.lang.String confSpon,
                                    java.lang.String confTheme,
                                    java.lang.String acronym)
        Generates Id for the given conference details . Conference name and number uniquely identifies a conference . If this key doesnt exist in the conf_ids map , new id is generated and also these conference details are inserted into the conference table
        Parameters:
        confDate - - date of Conference
        confName - - name of the conference
        confNum - - conference number
        confLoc - - conference location
        confSpon - - conference sponsor
        confTheme - - conference theme
        acronym - - acronym of the conference
        Returns:
        - generated Id for this conference

      • getCategoryId

        public java.lang.String getCategoryId(java.lang.String subject)
        Generates Id for the give category subject. If this category doesn't exist in the category_ids map, new Id is generated and also this category is inserted into category table
        Parameters:
        subject - - subject of category
        Returns:
        - generated Id for this category

      • getVolumeId

        public java.lang.String getVolumeId(java.lang.String journalTitle,
                           java.lang.String journalId,
                           java.lang.String volume,
                           java.lang.String issue,
                           java.lang.String publisherName)
        Generates Id for the given volume details . Combination of journalTitle + volume+issue is defined as unique key. If key doesn't exist in vol_ids table , new key generated and also insert into the volume insert values to create a new row for this volume
        Parameters:
        volId - - generated Volume Id
        vol - - volume of the article
        issue - - issue of the article
        journalId - - journal id from journal-meta
        journalTitle - - journal title from journal-meta
        publisherName - - publisher name from journal-meta
        Returns:
        - generate volumeId for this volume
